caption: Favorite queso dip in Chicago! They have delicious food, a great ambiance, and very friendly staff. Their rooftop patio is really nice too!  Their margaritas are delicious and also SO strong! I miss their happy hours pre-pandemic, the truck stop nachos were amazing! Delicious burritos too.  One of my favorite spots overall and, as a brand designer, I appreciate everything about their branding and overall aesthetic.
Great cocktails, incredible burritos, and to-die-for salsa.

I absolutely loved this place. The spicy margarita pitcher was incredible. I had the chicken, steak and shrimp taco. Was t thrilled with the chicken taco but the steak and shrimp were absolutely delicious. Would go back. The rooftop seating is awesome and even though it’s closed because of COVID, the indoor space looked really sleek, too.
Delicious drinks and brunch! I would definitely recommend their rooftop patio when it is warm enough. They are great with social distancing tables.

I ordered Lonesome Rose’s nachos from Uber eats. First let me tell you how much I miss their truck nachos on a summer patio of day drinking with their slushy margarita drinks to wash them down. Second, when ordering for delivery which is what I did, usually special instructions include asking for something on the side like ranch or extra sauce... and even then do you ever get what you ask for? I’d say 50/50. Well... I ordered their truck nachos and it said 60-70 minute delivery window (based on demand) and requested my chips be separated from the topping. My order arrived and I was just sooo impressed and happy!! I honestly just expected all the toppings to be put together in a side dish (at best).. or just exactly what I ordered altogether and nachos all in one but soggy bc they sat so long on the way to be delivered.. BUT! They packaged each and every ingredient individually so I could make my own fresh nachos at home. Can’t say it’s as good as their masterpiece they make themselves.. but omg.. still so good!!! And crunchy and fresh! Again, so impressed and so pleased at the lengths they went to fulfill my request. Thank you so much lonesome rose!! Soooooo delicious as always. Customer for life.

I seriously cannot get over how delicious Lonesome Rose is. Every menu item we've ordered is flavorful, creative, and soo fresh. I may actually be addicted the queso and their slushy cocktails. Huge fan of the brunch too.

We ordered fish tacos, a burrito, nachos, and their horchata. The food was delicious. The horchata was probably the worst horchata we have tried in Chicago. It did not even taste like horchata, and for $6 for a small, we expected a lot more. For that reason, I deducted one star. Great food, bad horchata.
(Translated by Google) Attention can be better  (Original) La atención puede ser mejor
love the food
Mexican food and the scene at this location is super good. Good place to catch up with friends. I'll return with my friends. The bill won't break you.

(Translated by Google) Last night at approximately 8 p.m. I went to the restaurant to pick up two deliveries, and despite the fact that one of them was already ready, I was waiting about 45 minutes for the other and it was not ready, and in that situation we were around 15 people waiting to pick up the orders, I did not return to that site to look for deliverys.  (Original) Anoche aproximadamente a las 8 p.m. fuí al restaurante a retirar dos deliverys, y a pesar de que uno de ellos ya  estaba listo, estuve esperando cerca de 45 minutos por el otro  y no  estuvo listo, y en esa situación estábamos alrededor de 15 personas  esperando por  retirar  los  pedidos, no regresp a ese sitio  a buscar  deliverys.

The food here was very good and I would recommend going here to get a burrito for sure. That being said I could suggest the carnitas one because I enjoyed that one much more than my steak one. The steak in the burrito was in strips which was strange for me and I didn’t like it as much. The queso is very good and the chips were great! That quesadilla was very good as well! A bit small honestly but good. I think I’ll be going back here for sure in the future.

My boyfriend and I ordered take out and we each got a burrito, me carnitas and him steak. We decided to share half and half and the carnitas one was really good. The steak was not. It was dry, tough, and just one flat piece. The quesadilla was surprisingly good for only being cheese. The queso dip was okay, but nothing to write home about. Tasted just like the jar stuff you can buy in the store. We did request for the take out at a specific time and they did have it ready so that was nice.
My top place for Mexican food. Don't fret if it's busy, it is worth the wait. I'll return with my coworkers. It has a good atmosphere.
Very friendly staff
Cool spot in Logan Square. Food was good, portion size seemed small for the price. Very cool Covid 19 measures are in place, you order from your phone, totally contact less. No menus or anything.
If any place deserves to weather 2020 it's this place.  Great food, hot cocktails, VERY safe protocols for dining.  Loved everything I ordered.  Highly recommend.
Good food, interesting decorations, okay staff

Ate there for lunch and it was so good! I got the vegetarian burrito and I was awesome because the flavor was perfect and they grill it to make it crispy! Just perfect! We got a pitcher of margaritas, which gave each about 6 drinks in all. I also got the bang bang dulce de leche pie and it was soooo tasty!!! Thanks again for great service, food, and drinks! I would definitely come again!

Their tacos are average for me, but the presentation was great and my friends enjoyed them. Their drinks and soft serve ice cream(horchata and Abuelita chocolate flavors) more than made up for it. Their service is great. I think I had someone come check on us every 8 mins(it caught my attention, so I decided to keep track...yeah I'm weird). Would go again to try different food items, but I'm really going back for their drinks and ice cream.
Best tacos in Chi City hands down. I’m lookin at you @BigStar & @BrokenEnglish 👀
Wonderful food and even better service! The staff was incredibly friendly, made wonderful recommendations and helped create a great atmosphere
The burrito was delicious every single item inside was extremely fresh and properly portioned! The server was a blonde guy-super nice! Will return and bring friends! Margarita was lit too!

This is not your traditional Mexican Taco restaurant BUT there are quite a few good choices here if you're looking to be adventurous. The burrito 🌯 wasn't bad with the choice of picadillo; kinda bummed their fire chicken was out for the season and they switched over to a seasonal offering of Pumpkin Mole. As I told ya, not traditional lol but quite unique. The mole isn't too spicy for people who can handle just a little bit of heat, this mole is for you.  The Baja 🐟 taco was perfectly fried and delicious to eat. The Horchata was creamy for sure and not too rich; just the right amount of balance. They are observing 6 feet apart when it come to table seating and it's quite spacious on the outdoor patio. Please be kind to the servers and wear your damn mask when asked to.  Overall, it's a cute Southwestern taco 🌮 type of vibe restaurant with unique creations for you to try.  P.S. Points to the person who can find the Lonely Rose
Overpriced corn $6 fir tiny portion
Breakfast tacos remind me of Austin. AMAZING.
Pretty good food to go along with some of the best COVID precautions I've seen in the neighborhood.
Incredible tacos and stout margs!
Great new Latin flavor. Ian the host was wonderful. So knowledgable! He should definitely be waiting tables!
Greatest brunch ever! Everything was delicious from the dishes to the drinks! Great service to boot.
Overall decent food. Kitchen closes at 8:45 pm on weekdays now. Barbacoa can be a bit greasy. Drinks are good.
It was our first time here and I enjoyed the food and service. It was delicious and the rooftop sitting was perfect.

Lonesome Rose is supposed to have an amazing rooftop I have yet to Make it up there but will soon.  The patio seating outside is nice comfortable and the service is here Is absolutely ducking amazing!  Th California Ave street corn is off the charts good!  A must order.  The Carnitas were very tasty with wonderful roasted flavor.  The El Dorado Supreme taco is a fully filled American Ground beef taco in a hard shell.  It hits the nostalgic taco feel for me.  This is going to be one of my favorite taco/margarita places for sure!  Woot Woot!

Nice ambiance but the service was not that great at all. Sat down at 8:30 and was immediately rushed to put an order in. Unfortunately the food was just not hitting. The guacamole was seasonless and the shrimp tacos just tasted so odd. My group and I got the margarita pitcher which is $61 and it tasted like watered down syrup. For the future I’ll have to my money else where.
Quality food and great service

I had previously rated this 5 starts. We live close by and get carryout from here AT LEAST once a week since they opened... If not more. Easily our favorite. However we've notice a decrease in quality and consistency in the last couple months. At first we gave the benefit of the doubt due to the current climate. However, we have decided it's not going to change. I would say 50% of the time the food isn't consistently made. Maybe different cooks make it differently?? Maybe shortage of ingredients?? I don't know. My favorite menu item is the Fire Chicken bowl.... Sometimes they leave off the kale... Today they substituted for maybe zucchini?? It was gross. We also get Carne Asada tacos a a lot, however sometimes they are completely flavorless. We always order extra salsa and they only remember it sometimes. At least we live close so we can just run across the street when they get it wrong or forget something. It is so sad because this is seriously our favorite, but I think we are going to stop coming here. Today before we ordered we said "one more chance" and it was horrible. We even tried out different times of the day... Thinking maybe it was leftovers at the end of the night... Still no. Again, so so so sad but this just isn't what it used to be. Maybe we will try again in a month or so.

Great rooftop and service. The carnita bowl was amazing. Not huge but enough and reasonably priced. Guac and queso was also fresh and the chips were great!! The margarita pitcher was okay, not super strong but not overpriced. Overall everything was amazing and I’ll definitely be back
Great food and drinks.  The roof top bar was fabulous.  It's covered to allow the light in,  but helps keep out the heat.
Great rooftop. Margaritas were top notch and the elotes were great too. My favorite taco was the Pork Shoulder.
It was good
Delicious and real cool food! Also the service always goes above and beyond

Lots of Organization, certainly one of the best restaurants in Chicago. Over 100 times, food is delivered in a fantastic time. In times as fast as the time specified in the application, cuisine, customer service note 1000. Congratulations for the Manager of this restaurant. You are a professional.
You feel safe while still being about enjoy a great meal and a delicious Margarita
Server was friendly. Hostess was rude. Margaritas were tasty. Ceasar was creative.
Excellent vibe, tasty food, reasonable prices. Very much enjoyed our visit. Corn OFF the cob was seriously amazing!

Ate here two times in the last week. The rooftop is tight but I'd be ok with sitting at the sidewalk tables. The ranch water is real good, reminds of the days of summer when you're a kid drink a cold bev after being outside with your friends all day. Except now I'm old and the water gets you buzzed. I got the baja burrito the first time and then the breakfast burrito the second time. The fish in the baja was super good. Let me talk about this breakfast burrito real quick. One word. Fluff. As in the fluffiest eggs I've ever had. Perfectly melted cheese and a zesty sauce on the side. One phrase comes to mind when I think of lonesome rose. "Oh hell yeah brother". Eat here, for real.
It was great

Arrived at 6:30 on Thurs nite.  Told it was a 45 minute wait to dine on their patio, where I have dined on before with my kids and their pups when visiting the city. When I realized after waiting 30 minutes that my kids were walking over with their pups and informed the host, I was told they did not allow dogs on their patio, and never had. Wrong, host guy, done it before, but whatever. When I said, ok I guess I'll have to place a to-go order, I was told 'sorry, we just closed take out orders.' So, its ok to leave me sitting here waiting an hour to sit and eat, but you wont serve me a taco to go? And without even a attempt at an apology from snotty host guy,  Just...'so I can take you off the list?' Bottom line, food is good here but not good enough to deal with this. Drove an hour, waited 30 minutes and left without a chip...or a taco. So,yes, you can most definitely take me off your list!
Yummy twist on tacos. The drinks are great!

Visited last night for dinner, waited about 20 mins for a table at 5pm. Great experience! Tables were very distanced and the waitress was double masked in this heat! No specials at this time since they aren’t able to seat as many tables but food was good and drinks were cold. Only item I would change is the quest dip...while tasty, it was SO thin...dripping everywhere! We’ll try the beans and chorizo in it next time!
Great taco Tuesday
Food was amazing. Ambiance was cool. Service was terrible. Hoping that was a fluke. I'll give it another try because the burrito and nachos were so good.
we love the atmosphere and service and food and drinks we love it all!!!! ❤️😌
Food was cold and without much flavor. Service was mostly absent. The drinks were good but that’s the only good thing today about this establishment.

The Taco Tuesday deal is disorientingly well priced for how good everything tastes. It’s not that other days of the week aren’t good times to come here, it’s just that coming on a Tuesday will make you feel all that much better about spending your dollars.
The staff is helpful for understanding dietary issues/ my gluten intolerance and the food and drinks are sooooo good!! Love the upstairs patio in the summer.
Very inconsistent service. Tacos are decent
If you're getting a burrito, get it smothered. You'll thank me later. You better thank me later.

Came Fri at 5. Frozen margaritas were not frozen and out of the other flavor. Bathrooms out of toilet paper. Tacos seem to have gone down since opening. Not sure if under new management but not as special as it used to be.
Kid friendly. Vegan/ vegetarian friendly
This place makes a really good spot to catch up with friends with great drinks and small plates + appetizers.
Good cocktails
Great brunch! Service and food is always consistently great. Prices are very reasonable
Good food, comfortable environment, friendly waitstaff.
Good queso, not enough chips

Firstly, the food here was great. It tasted healthy despite being delicious and nothing felt greasy or overly filling. The restaurant itself is also very charming in a simple and minimalist kind of way. I heard the roof deck is awesome but alas it was raining when I went.  However, I had to take 2 stars off for the service. As others have already pointed out, the restaurant is consistently out of the beer on their menu. I ordered one and was told it was out. I then ordered another, listed under their “Beers on Tap” list, and was brought a can. When I asked about it, I was told that they were also out of the draft of that beer. The can was already open so I couldn’t switch it out and I wasn’t even brought a glass with it. If I wanted canned beer, I could have stayed home.  I then ordered a second beer with my food and had to wait nearly 20 minutes before it was finally brought out. I would have thought the waitress forgot about it, but two of my friends also had to wait for their drinks. They all finally came out together... but we were nearly done with our meal by then.  I would probably come back, but maybe only for a casual lunch. Would not recommend for dinner.
Great tacos and drinks. Cool space.
Great happy hour menu
Queso + margs are 👍👍
Good food and reasonable prices too. The only problem is that if you order a bowl (what I'd recommend) you need to make sure your friends order other bowls so you can try them all!

We had just gotten to Chicago from Ontario, Canada. Every restaurant was packed, and my blood sugar was so low - luckily we found Lonesome Rose. I'm a complete novice with Mexican food, our waitress was incredibly helpful and the food was fresh and delicious. Dessert was amazing! Will definitely be back!

Veggie bowl is scrumdidlyumptious! Mushroom Mole tacos are great (leave off cheese to veganize). The burritos are just okay.  It has a nice rooftop if you don’t mind the wait. The waitstaff is hit or miss. The interior is comfortable with lots of natural light. Worth a visit.

I absolutely can't get enough of the queso here.  you get the breakfast sandwich every time- hands down. That's what you do, tacos are amazing as well. This place is beyond what you think it is. YUGE fan.

The decor here is what shines bright. Light wood walls and furniture with attention to detail in the table decorations. Truly a upscale Tex-Mex vibe. And the food is delicous. Grab a frozen marg and their huge nachos at happy hour and you will be happy as well.
Fabulous tacos. Loved the brisket taco. The street corn was awesome.

The staff was friendly and our food was prepared quickly. Didn't have to wait long without a reservation on a friday night which was awesome. Menu has a nice variety with some great complimentary cocktails.
Great!
Great Happy Hour ... Margaritas and food on point!

The staff and drinks were okay. Skip Lonesome Rose and head to the bar within the bar, Golden Teardrops. That place had delicious cocktails, awesome ambience (esp over the holiday season), and the staff was super nice.

AVOID AT ALL COSTS!!! This place is absolutely dreadful. After we sat down, we received our tray of chips and salsa, and we ordered two pitchers of margaritas, that cost 38 dollars. The pitchers were half full and served three margaritas, when an individual one costs ten dollars. I was told by management that they make up for the lack of volume by the additional tequila that is added to the pitcher. She proceeded to argue with me for a solid fifteen minutes about how it "equals out." After said argument she offered to bring a free margarita to make up for it, which had absolutely no alchohol in it. She was incredibly rude and argumentative. I will never return here and I will try to the best of my ability to make sure nobody ever comes to this joke of an establishment.
Nicest people on earth. Friendliest vibe. But how on earth could this place get a Michelin Bib Gourmand award?  Come on.  Something's up.
Amazing place with big food selection and cocktails
Just went for drinks but will be back for the food next time.

The waiter was nice but forgot EVERYTHING we asked him for. Asked him 3 times for homemade salsa and didn’t bring it until the fourth. I tried ordering the brisket, they ran out. I tried ordering the veggie, that was out too. Proceeded to order drinks, which took forever. My dad ordered a Modelo, it was ridiculously flat, didn’t even make a sound then he cracked it open. We told the waiter, he brought the second and the same exact thing. Instead we opted for a margarita, didn’t get that until 15 minutes later. The food came out fast but was COLD. And lastly, we get the bill and they forget to take off the 2 flat Modelos from the bill. NEVER going back.
$6 for a horchata served in a tiny glass absurd. Each refill is another $6. Save your money and go to Big Star
Bougie tacos, delicious drinks, karaoke in the basement!! An excellent combo.
I like to go here for Brunch tacos!

Food and drinks were amazing. Music was too loud. Do not, for the love of god, expect to split a check. They will only offer an even split and then if you ask for a split by seat, will leave you to do all the math yourself. A terrible customer experience!

The restaurant itself was very nice. There rooftop is an especially good place to sit, weather permitting. The prices are really good. You can get a Lone Star beer and a shot of whiskey for only$6. Food was tasty. I had the pork belly, chicken tinga, and mushroom mole tacos. Only complaint is that the corn tortillas were cold so they were a bit stuff and chewy. I was a little disappointed since they claim they make them in house.  If they had been warm,I think it would be a whole different story.  Staff was attentive and friendly.

Everything was excellent. Cute location, decor, and the food was so flavorful. Not quite fast casual so allow for enough time. Schwarma and rice were sooo good along with the 4 sides you can choose! Healthy portions (too much for one sitting which is great!) and the pita was warm and fresh. Finally we had coffee and beignets afterward which were to die for!
A 5-star Veggie burrito 👌
We always go for the fancy choco taco, and it's always delicious! Their tacos are good too 👍
Went here for brunch on Sunday. What a great surprise this place was. Great brunch menu and the food was amazing. Really cool interior and as a bonus they have a deck on the roof for more seating.
Great cocktails and delicious food... and save room for a homemade choco taco!
Nice brunch at the bar. Also very nice rooftop deck for drinks and food. Very friendly service.
Fantastic rooftop with amazing food. Great for dates.
Drinks are great, food is mediocre
good brunch burrito

Virtue Rose Cider (top), Crispy Pork Belly (left), Mushrooms in Mole (right) The cider was okay, the pork belly was over cooked. Pork belly should be juicey, tender and fatty this was dry, chewy and the fat was super crispy. The Mushrooms in Mole was good, nice sized mushroom pieces.  Staff was great, wasn't busy at the bar.

Lonesome Rose has consistently good food, especially tacos and the Truck Stop nachos. Solid options at their full bar as well as a few interesting mixed drink options. Patio upstairs is nice in the summer. Golden Teardrops downstairs is a cool place to hang out, though it is small and gets pretty crowded and the music can be a bit too loud.
Delicious!!!
Cool atmosphere and friendly staff.
Amazing food and Excellent service
Excellent food and service, awesome rooftop seating.
It's a nice place. The basement bar is really cool. I'm not super impressed by the food, despite its high critical acclaim. It is affordable.
Fantastic food, creative drinks, and one of the best margaritas ever!
It's loud in there, I dont mind it but its not the place to go if you want to have a deep conversation. However, service is always great, food is simple, good (not great) and its reasonably priced.
Food is great. Staff is usually friendly. Must try the veggie burrito and the queso dip. Micheladas are also good.
Great Mexican food.
The food is delicious but pricey. The service is extremely slow...we sat at our table without a drink order for at least 30-40 minutes.

From the look of the menu, it looked an ok place. However dont be fooled, the Google and Yelp does not have the entire menu. There are quite few vegetarian and vegan options. We ordered the vegetarian burrito and vegan taco. They were both amazing. Their  queso was amazing. On top great service. This place has a rooftop as well.
Great margarita on a perfect day
Service was nice but food lacked flavor, especially for the price.
Great desserts
Nice outdoor space. The tacos were delicious. The Chaco Taco was dangerously good.
Best fish tacos in the city. Great drinks. Only down side is that you can feel like the staff isn't as attentive as it should be
Superb bar staff and delicious food. Highly recommend. Oh and the tequila/mescal is fabulous and somewhat dangerous :)

I finally went to Lonesome Rose after dragging my feet for a long time, and I am officially obsessed. The prices are really reasonable - I have cravings for the $4 Grilled Cheese Quesadilla. Yes, sometimes the service can be a little slow / something might be missed, and yes, sometimes they are out of things I wish they weren't out of, but it is the perfect spot for a summer evening. Will continue to be back again and again for the elotes, guac, and quesadilla. So good.

The bright, relaxed, and friendly atmosphere made for a perfect place to catch up with friends over brunch. There was a variety of options, so there was something for everyone. Can't recommend the french toast enough, but everything we tried was delicious!
Happy hour from 3-6 weekdays but we enjoy drinks and food here anytime.  Great "Swirl" mezcal drinks

This is one of my favorite places in Chicago! You can get a delicious meal with drinks for two people for less than $50 (if you get beer instead of cocktails, you can do it for less than $40). The atmosphere is great for dates, but I've also taken my parents here before and had a good time. It's casual, but feels a couple steps above your average casual restaurant in Chicago.
Great rooftop and tacos

Very nice service though the bar staff was slightly pretentious. Food was good and drinks were good as well and standard competitive prices.  Overall good experience,  high quality eats and they do allow substitutions.

The drink selection wasn't great, and they seemed to be out of a lot of beers I was hoping to have. We sat inside because there was a private event on the rooftop, which was disappointing on such a nice day. It is VERY loud in there, not because the people were loud but the space just reverberates sound everywhere. It is pretty inside, and I did really enjoy the plants all around. The tacos (pork, and barbacoa) were pretty good, 4 out of 5. But I think there are definitely better places to have tacos in the city
Delicious bowls.
Love everything about this place, from the understated yet gorgeous dining room, the food and cocktails.

I’ve been here a couple of times now, both brunch and dinner. The food is meh at best, and the service was terrible. My friend asked if the chef could leave beans out of her burrito, the server never asked the chef and brought her the burrito anyways, and then told her to “pick the beans out.” If you’re looking for good Mexican food, go somewhere else.
Food was absolutely outstanding. The service, however, was really bad. As 4 people that work in a restaurant, we got some of the worst service I've ever had in a restaurant
First time there it was excellent the Truck stop Nachos are the chain!

We love Lonesome Rose! Delicious tacos, great drinks, and an awesome rooftop (although I am missing the al pastor tacos - please bring them back)! So glad we have this gem in our neighborhood. I want to thank the staff/management for taking care of us after our pick up order was severely delayed. We appreciate the good service and will be back soon!
You come here for the atmosphere then stay for the food. I think this place does both great. Cool enough for a date spot and cheap enough for a quick bite.
Avocado toast w egg is really good. Tacos are also good.
Very special spot!

Three stars are for our very attentive backwaiter,waiter and hostess. Tacos were alright. Better off going to Taqueria Moran up the street. They were out of a drink or two per ingredients. Also out of two flavors of soft serve ice cream my friend was looking forward to trying. Not enough menu choices. Nice to checkout but Chicago has a lot better taco menus out there.

Excellent service and ambiance. Will go again.  UPDATE: I came again. This time I ordered food to go. They won't do togo orders over they phone you have to use the Caviar app which is standard for some restaurants.  In this case I was close by so walked in and ordered from the bar. Excellent service. The food came quickly and the bar area is AMAZING! Nicely decorated with plenty of room and helpful staff.

Offering a cool interior design and happy hour specials, I frequent this place for my nacho cravings. Customer service is pretty much non existent, after visiting several times I've realized you will not see your server again after your order is taken. You might even have to chase them down for your bill. Parking is kind of easy on early weekdays and a nightmare in the evening.
(Translated by Google) Chicken tinga tacos!  (Original) Chicken tinga tacos!

Tried it on a whim.. was in the area... and was pleasantly surprised... Not crowded, and the service was excellent... friendly, fast and waitress gave us great suggestions... Had the mushroom mole tacos, the fish tacos, the chicken tacos and the barbacoa nachos. All were great...Chips were handmade on site...Could have used a little bigger and better draft beer list.  Would go back for sure... One of the better TexMex, casual experiences on the north side.
Great rooftop patio
The food, the drinks, the service ❤️
Not very friendly!
Good margs
One of the best, if not the best, places to eat in Logan Square
Affordable upscaled Mexican restaurant. Great food. Good margarita. Superior service. Lots of neighborhood locals.
Average food, wasn’t bad...just forgettable. Subpar service at best. Wouldn’t go out of my way to go back. Not sure what the rave reviews are about.
We order carry out from here often and will not be ordering again. The staff is apathetic to carry out orders and they changed carry out containers so there is less food in the bowls.
Rooftop vibes were perfect
The choco taco is a great sweet snack! I added a vegan taco on to my regular tacos as a change of pace, and it was delicious with a serious spicy kick!

When we arrived, our hostess told us that the wait would be about 45 minutes because the upstairs outdoor area was very busy and there were no spots upstairs. We asked if there was a bar up there that we could wait at, she told us no there was not. Upon our own investigation, we found that there were numerous open tables which remained open. We also found the upstairs bar that we were told was nonexistent. I’m unsure as to why she told us these things. Our bartender and out waiter were kind. They did get my order wrong but they fixed it decently quick. The food was good but nothing amazing that you wouldn’t be able to get elsewhere. Overall, being told to wait for a table for 0 reason, really gave us a bad impression of this place.
Great place for artisanal cocktails and Latin food.
Gooooood margs. The guy from Vine was my server and super nice. Always good to see a familiar face even if it's at a Mexican restaurant you've never been to before. Good patio too!!!!
Drinks were good and so was the food. I had the mushroom mole tacos.  The tacos feel a pricey if you ask me.
Really really good burrito!
Food is pretty meh (the cheese dip tastes like cheez whiz) and service is reeeaaaally slow. Nice patio though!
A little slow. Breakfast was good.
Good food, friendly staff, small but tasty drinks, kinda loud and echoey, but both of us had a good time overall. Great burrito, good  nachos and queso.
Amazing!!
Place is kinda dead the last few times ive been here

If you're in the Logan Square area of Chicago this is a great place for Mexican/Tex-Mex food.  Start with their guacamole and chips, or their Chile con queso.  Their crispy pork belly bowl was superb. Cocktails well crafted Mezcal margaritas  and bloody Mary's were great.  Will definitely return for more next time we are in town.

Had a wonderful evening on the roof enjoying Happy Hour with my girlfriend. We shared some pretty amazing nachos and each ordered some tacos. I had fish, pork belly and pulled chicken and they were all fantastic. It's a great spot to relax after a long day or catch up with friends and share some great food!
Food was good but service was very slow and disorganize. I hope they can work on it because the place is great.

Amazing! Went here with a group of people for the first time and it was awesome. Really amazing mexican food. I'm from Arizona and have had some great mexican food. This was on par. Tacos were unique with terrific meat. I got the pork belly and barbacoa. The appetizers were perfect -  got the street corn, guacamole, nachos and queso. Also had their house margarita that was perfect, with the perfect amount of salt on the rim. Will definitely be going back.
Good tacos!

Not that this matters from a review standpoint, but I'm obsessed with the decor and lighting of this place.  If you do look at the menu via Yelp, it's very abbreviated. It could just be because their menus change frequently depending on the season, but just know that there are a few more options.  It sounds basic, but you should get the guacamole. The chips are good, because they're not too greasy, but warm and crunchy. Everything you'd want in a chip, really. I've gotten the shrimp tacos, baja fish tacos, and the fire chicken. Everything was equally good, and extremely fresh. I unfortunately can't eat pork, but I've been with people who ordered the al pastor, and it looks fantastic.  I'm going to get real Midwest here, but the portions are a bit smaller. This isn't a bad thing at all though, because what I hate most about tacos is sometimes you want to try a couple different ones, but you're way too full.  What's good about this is that service is great, so if you want to put in an extra order of something you can.  Also, the drinks are worth trying, as well. I reluctantly ordered the frozen margarita my first time there thinking it was going to be way too sweet. It was not. I've read some complaints here about wait times. Any time I've gone here, it was a Saturday at around 4:00, and it was empty. I know it's not an ideal dinner time, but it's something to keep in mind.

Lonesome Rose intrigues with a good ol dive bar name while still being nestled in between two of the best neighborhoods in Chicago - Logan Square and Bucktown. On any given night you might find yourself making friends at the bar or leaning over the hardwood tables to kiss your date. Extra points if your visiting when it's raining ;P The first time I visited with my girlfriend we really enjoyed the a la carte tacos but the title track draft arrived to our table in a lukewarm mug. It was fine but after asking our server if we could get the next round a little cooler the manager came to our table, introduced herself and gave us two ice cold Lonesome Roses in equally ice cold mugs. She did not charge us for them. It was a nice gesture that had us visiting again a couple weeks later. The lighting stays low and you'll feel like a true hipster elite in this restaurant and bar. Visit if you're with someone worth impressing. Visit again for the cocktails.
